<!-- What is AI Readiness -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>What is AI Readiness?</h2>
        <p>When someone asks ChatGPT "Who can fix my roof in Cape Town?" or uses Google's AI Overview, these systems don't just search keywords. They look for businesses that clearly state what they do in a way machines can understand.</p>
        <p>AI Readiness means your website has:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Structured data</strong> that tells machines your business facts</li>
          <li><strong>Clear content</strong> that states what you offer</li>
          <li><strong>Schema markup</strong> that identifies your services</li>
          <li><strong>Machine-readable signals</strong> that AI can extract and cite</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Without these elements, AI systems have to guess what your business does, and they often guess wrong or skip you entirely.</p>
        <a href="/learn/ai-readiness/" class="btn btn-secondary">Learn More About AI Readiness</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mb-2">Quick Example</h3>
        <p><strong>Without Schema:</strong></p>
        <p class="text-muted">"Welcome to ABC Company! We've been serving customers since 1995 with quality and dedication..."</p>
        <p class="mb-2"><em>AI thinks: "Some company that's been around a while. Not sure what they do."</em></p>
        <p><strong>With Schema:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>{
  "@@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "ABC Plumbing",
  "serviceType": "Plumbing",
  "areaServed": "Cape Town"
}</code></pre>
        <p><em>AI knows: "Plumbing company in Cape Town."</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

